{"type":"message","id":"427f110d","parentId":"5b5a6903","timestamp":"2026-03-30T06:39:47.542Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'll create a comprehensive terminal commands reference chart for you. Let me write it to a file:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"functions.write:24","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/admin/.openclaw/workspace/terminal-commands.md","content":"# Terminal Commands Reference\n\n## 📁 FILE & DIRECTORY OPERATIONS\n\n| Command | Usage | Description |\n|---------|-------|-------------|\n| `ls` | `ls -la` | List files and directories |\n| `cd` | `cd /path/to/dir` | Change directory |\n| `pwd` | `pwd` | Print working directory |\n| `mkdir` | `mkdir newdir` | Create directory |\n| `rm` | `rm -rf file` | Remove file/directory |\n| `cp` | `cp source dest` | Copy files |\n| `mv` | `mv old new` | Move/rename files |\n| `touch` | `touch file.txt` | Create empty file |\n| `cat` | `cat file.txt` | Display file contents |\n| `less` | `less file.txt` | View file with pagination |\n| `head` | `head -20 file.txt` | Show first N lines |\n| `tail` | `tail -f log.txt` | Show last lines, follow changes |\n| `find` | `find . -name \"*.js\"` | Search for files |\n| `locate` | `locate filename` | Find files by name (faster) |\n\n---\n\n## 🔍 VIEWING & EDITING\n\n| Command | Usage | Description |\n|---------|-------|-------------|\n| `nano` | `nano file.txt` | Simple text editor |\n| `vim` | `vim file.txt` | Powerful text editor |\n| `grep` | `grep \"pattern\" file` | Search text in files |\n| `awk` | `awk '{print $1}' file` | Text processing |\n| `sed` | `sed 's/old/new/g' file` | Stream editor |\n| `wc` | `wc -l file.txt` | Count lines/words/bytes |\n| `sort` | `sort file.txt` | Sort lines |\n| `uniq` | `uniq -c file.txt` | Remove duplicate lines |\n| `diff` | `diff file1 file2` | Compare files |\n| `file` | `file filename` | Determine file type |\n\n---\n\n## ⚙️ SYSTEM & PROCESS MANAGEMENT\n\n| Command | Usage | Description |\n|---------|-------|-------------|\n| `ps` | `ps aux` | List running processes |\n| `top` | `top` | Interactive process viewer |\n| `htop` | `htop` | Better process viewer |\n| `kill` | `kill -9 PID` | Terminate process |\n| `killall` | `killall processname` | Kill by name |\n| `df` | `df -h` | Disk space usage |\n| `du` | `du -sh directory` | Directory size |\n| `free` | `free -h` | Memory usage |\n| `uptime` | `uptime` | System uptime |\n| `whoami` | `whoami` | Current user |\n| `id` | `id` | User/group info |\n| `uname` | `uname -a` | System information |\n| `env` | `env` | Environment variables |\n| `history` | `history` | Command history |\n| `clear` | `clear` | Clear screen |\n\n---\n\n## 🌐 NETWORKING\n\n| Command | Usage | Description |\n|---------|-------|-------------|\n| `ping` | `ping google.com` | Test connectivity |\n| `curl` | `curl -O URL` | Transfer data from URL |\n| `wget` | `wget URL` | Download files |\n| `ssh` | `ssh user@host` | Secure shell login |\n| `scp` | `scp file user@host:/path` | Secure copy |\n| `rsync` | `rsync -avz src dest` | Sync files efficiently |\n| `netstat` | `netstat -tlnp` | Network connections |\n| `ss` | `ss -tlnp` | Socket statistics (newer) |\n| `lsof` | `lsof -i :8080` | List open files/ports |\n| `ifconfig` | `ifconfig` | Network interfaces |\n| `ip` | `ip addr` | Modern network tool |\n| `traceroute` | `traceroute host` | Trace network path |\n| `dig` | `dig domain.com` | DNS lookup |\n| `nslookup` | `nslookup domain.com` | DNS query |\n| `nc` | `nc -zv host port` | Netcat - network swiss army knife |\n| `telnet` | `telnet host port` | Test port connectivity |\n\n---\n\n## 🔐 PERMISSIONS & OWNERSHIP\n\n| Command | Usage | Description |\n|---------|-------|-------------|\n| `chmod` | `chmod 755 file` | Change file permissions |\n| `chown` | `chown user:group file` | Change file owner |\n| `sudo` | `sudo command` | Run as superuser |\n| `su` | `su - username` | Switch user |\n| `passwd` | `passwd` | Change password |\n| `groups` | `groups username` | Show user groups |\n\n---\n\n## 📦 PACKAGE MANAGEMENT\n\n### Debian/Ubuntu (apt)\n| Command | Usage | Description |\n|---------|-------|-------------|\n| `apt update` | `sudo apt update` | Update package list |\n| `apt upgrade` | `sudo apt upgrade` | Upgrade packages |\n| `apt install` | `sudo apt install pkg` | Install package |\n| `apt remove` | `sudo apt remove pkg` | Remove package |\n| `apt search` | `apt search keyword` | Search packages |\n\n### RHEL/CentOS (yum/dnf)\n| Command | Usage | Description |\n|---------|-------|-------------|\n| `yum install` | `sudo yum install pkg` | Install package |\n| `dnf install` | `sudo dnf install pkg` | Install package (newer) |\n\n### Arch (pacman)\n| Command | Usage | Description |\n|---------|-------|-------------|\n| `pacman -S` | `sudo pacman -S pkg` | Install package |\n| `pacman -R` | `sudo pacman -R pkg` | Remove package |\n| `pacman -Sy` | `sudo pacman -Sy` | Update database |\n\n---\n\n## 🔧 ARCHIVE & COMPRESSION\n\n| Command | Usage | Description |\n|---------|-------|-------------|\n| `tar` | `tar -czvf archive.tar.gz dir` | Create tar.gz archive |\n| `tar` | `tar -xzvf archive.tar.gz` | Extract tar.gz |\n| `gzip` | `gzip file.txt` | Compress with gzip |\n| `gunzip` | `gunzip file.gz` | Decompress gzip |\n| `zip` | `zip -r archive.zip dir` | Create zip archive |\n| `unzip` | `unzip archive.zip` | Extract zip |\n\n---\n\n## 🔄 JOB CONTROL\n\n| Command | Usage | Description |\n|---------|-------|-------------|\n| `&` | `command &` | Run in background |\n| `bg` | `bg %1` | Resume job in background |\n| `fg` | `fg %1` | Bring job to foreground |\n| `jobs` | `jobs` | List background jobs |\n| `nohup` | `nohup command &` | Run immune to hangups |\n| `disown` | `disown %1` | Remove job from shell |\n| `screen` | `screen -S session` | Terminal multiplexer |\n| `tmux` | `tmux new -s session` | Modern terminal multiplexer |\n\n---\n\n## 🔗 REDIRECTION & PIPES\n\n| Operator | Usage | Description |\n|----------|-------|-------------|\n| `>` | `cmd > file` | Redirect stdout to file (overwrite) |\n| `>>` | `cmd >> file` | Redirect stdout (append) |\n| `2>` | `cmd 2> error.log` | Redirect stderr |\n| `&>` | `cmd &> all.log` | Redirect stdout and stderr |\n| `<` | `cmd < file` | Redirect stdin from file |\n| `\\|` | `cmd1 \\| cmd2` | Pipe output to next command |\n| `\\|\\|` | `cmd1 \\|\\| cmd2` | OR - run cmd2 if cmd1 fails |\n| `&&` | `cmd1 && cmd2` | AND - run cmd2 if cmd1 succeeds |\n| `;` | `cmd1 ; cmd2` | Run sequentially |\n\n---\n\n## 🛠️ ADVANCED / LESSER-USED COMMANDS\n\n| Command | Usage | Description |\n|---------|-------|-------------|\n| `strace` | `strace -p PID` | Trace system calls |\n| `ltrace` | `ltrace command` | Trace library calls |\n| `perf` | `perf top` | Performance analysis |\n| `vmstat` | `vmstat 1` | Virtual memory stats |\n| `iostat` | `iostat -x 1` | I/O statistics |\n| `mpstat` | `mpstat -P ALL 1` | CPU statistics per core |\n| `sar` | `sar -u 1` | System activity reporter |\n| `dmesg` | `dmesg \\| tail` | Kernel ring buffer |\n| `journalctl` | `journalctl -xe` | Systemd logs |\n| `systemctl` | `systemctl status service` | Control systemd services |\n| `watch` | `watch -n 1 'command'` | Run command periodically |\n| `timeout` | `timeout 5s command` | Run with time limit |\n| `nohup` | `nohup command &` | Ignore hangup signal |\n| `nice` | `nice -n 10 command` | Run with adjusted priority |\n| `renice` | `renice -n 5 -p PID` | Change running process priority |\n| `chroot` | `chroot /newroot /bin/bash` | Change root directory |\n| `mount` | `mount /dev/sdb1 /mnt` | Mount filesystem |\n| `umount` | `umount /mnt` | Unmount filesystem |\n| `fdisk` | `sudo fdisk -l` | Partition table manipulator |\n| `parted` | `sudo parted /dev/sda` | Partition editor |\n| `mkfs` | `mkfs.ext4 /dev/sdb1` | Create filesystem |\n| `fsck` | `fsck /dev/sdb1` | Filesystem check |\n| `dd` | `dd if=/dev/zero of=file bs=1M` | Convert and copy files |\n| `tee` | `command \\| tee file` | Output to file and stdout |\n| `xargs` | `find . -name \"*.txt\" \\| xargs rm` | Build and execute commands |\n| `parallel` | `parallel command ::: args` | Run commands in parallel |\n| `at` | `echo \"cmd\" \\| at now + 1 hour` | Schedule one-time task |\n| `cron` | `crontab -e` | Schedule recurring tasks |\n| `logger` | `logger \"message\"` | Write to system log |\n| `script` | `script session.log` | Record terminal session |\n"}},{"type":"text","text":"|"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"dashscope-coding","model":"kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774852568331}}
