{"type":"message","id":"bf4bbe5d","parentId":"5e3e289b","timestamp":"2026-03-30T06:44:11.895Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The chart is too long to send in one message. Let me split it into sections:\n\n---\n\n# Terminal Commands Reference\n\n## 📁 FILE & DIRECTORY OPERATIONS\n\n| Command | Usage | Description |\n|---------|-------|-------------|\n| `ls` | `ls -la` | List files and directories |\n| `cd` | `cd /path/to/dir` | Change directory |\n| `pwd` | `pwd` | Print working directory |\n| `mkdir` | `mkdir newdir` | Create directory |\n| `rm` | `rm -rf file` | Remove file/directory |\n| `cp` | `cp source dest` | Copy files |\n| `mv` | `mv old new` | Move/rename files |\n| `touch` | `touch file.txt` | Create empty file |\n| `cat` | `cat file.txt` | Display file contents |\n| `less` | `less file.txt` | View file with pagination |\n| `head` | `head -20 file.txt` | Show first N lines |\n| `tail` | `tail -f log.txt` | Show last lines, follow changes |\n| `find` | `find . -name \"*.js\"` | Search for files |\n| `locate` | `locate filename` | Find files by name (faster) |\n\n---\n\n## 🔍 VIEWING & EDITING\n\n| Command | Usage | Description |\n|---------|-------|-------------|\n| `nano` | `nano file.txt` | Simple text editor |\n| `vim` | `vim file.txt` | Powerful text editor |\n| `grep` | `grep \"pattern\" file` | Search text in files |\n| `awk` | `awk '{print $1}' file` | Text processing |\n| `sed` | `sed 's/old/new/g' file` | Stream editor |\n| `wc` | `wc -l file.txt` | Count lines/words/bytes |\n| `sort` | `sort file.txt` | Sort lines |\n| `uniq` | `uniq -c file.txt` | Remove duplicate lines |\n| `diff` | `diff file1 file2` | Compare files |\n| `file` | `file filename` | Determine file type |\n\n---\n\n## ⚙️ SYSTEM & PROCESS MANAGEMENT\n\n| Command | Usage | Description |\n|---------|-------|-------------|\n| `ps` | `ps aux` | List running processes |\n| `top` | `top` | Interactive process viewer |\n| `htop` | `htop` | Better process viewer |\n| `kill` | `kill -9 PID` | Terminate process |\n| `killall` | `killall processname` | Kill by name |\n| `df` | `df -h` | Disk space usage |\n| `du` | `du -sh directory` | Directory size |\n| `free` | `free -h` | Memory usage |\n| `uptime` | `uptime` | System uptime |\n| `whoami` | `whoami` | Current user |\n| `id` | `id` | User/group info |\n| `uname` | `uname -a` | System information |\n| `env` | `env` | Environment variables |\n| `history` | `history` | Command history |\n| `clear` | `clear` | Clear screen |\n\n---\n\nWant me to continue with the next sections (Networking, Permissions, Package Management, etc.)?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"dashscope-coding","model":"kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774853033104}}
{"type":"message","id":"d3ce3dec","parentId":"bf4bbe5d","timestamp":"2026-03-30T06:44:50.102Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Mon 2026-03-30 14:44 GMT+8] change the usage to inchude how to use it"}],"timestamp":1774853090098}}
{"type":"message","id":"004ab434","parentId":"d3ce3dec","timestamp":"2026-03-30T06:50:41.153Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'll update the chart with clearer usage instructions. Let me rewrite it:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"functions.write:25","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/admin/.openclaw/workspace/terminal-commands.md","content":"# Terminal Commands Reference\n\n## 📁 FILE & DIRECTORY OPERATIONS\n\n| Command | How to Use | What It Does |\n|---------|------------|--------------|\n| `ls` | Type `ls` to list files, `ls -la` for detailed view including hidden files | Lists files and directories |\n| `cd` | Type `cd foldername` to enter a folder, `cd ..` to go up, `cd ~` to go home | Changes your current directory |\n| `pwd` | Just type `pwd` and press Enter | Shows the full path of where you are |\n| `mkdir` | Type `mkdir newfolder` to create a folder | Creates a new directory |\n| `rm` | Type `rm filename` to delete a file, `rm -r folder` for directories | Deletes files or folders |\n| `cp` | Type `cp file.txt backup.txt` to copy a file | Copies files or directories |\n| `mv` | Type `mv oldname.txt newname.txt` to rename, or `mv file.txt /path/` to move | Moves or renames files |\n| `touch` | Type `touch newfile.txt` to create an empty file | Creates an empty file or updates timestamp |\n| `cat` | Type `cat file.txt` to display contents | Shows the entire contents of a file |\n| `less` | Type `less file.txt`, use arrows to scroll, `q` to quit | View large files page by page |\n| `head` | Type `head file.txt` or `head -20 file.txt` for 20 lines | Shows the beginning of a file |\n| `tail` | Type `tail file.txt` or `tail -f log.txt` to watch live | Shows the end of a file |\n| `find` | Type `find . -name \"*.js\"` to find all JS files | Searches for files by name |\n| `locate` | Type `locate filename` (faster than find) | Quickly finds files by name |\n\n---\n\n## 🔍 VIEWING & EDITING\n\n| Command | How to Use | What It Does |\n|---------|------------|--------------|\n| `nano` | Type `nano file.txt`, edit, then `Ctrl+O` to save, `Ctrl+X` to exit | Simple text editor |\n| `vim` | Type `vim file.txt`, press `i` to edit, `Esc` then `:wq` to save and quit | Advanced text editor |\n| `grep` | Type `grep \"error\" log.txt` to find lines with \"error\" | Searches for text patterns |\n| `awk` | Type `awk '{print $1}' file.txt` to print first column | Processes text by columns |\n| `sed` | Type `sed 's/old/new/g' file.txt` to replace text | Stream editor for transformations |\n| `wc` | Type `wc file.txt` or `wc -l file.txt` for line count only | Counts lines, words, bytes |\n| `sort` | Type `sort file.txt` or `sort -r file.txt` for reverse | Sorts lines alphabetically |\n| `uniq` | Type `uniq file.txt` or `uniq -c` to count duplicates | Removes duplicate lines |\n| `diff` | Type `diff file1.txt file2.txt` | Shows differences between files |\n| `file` | Type `file filename` | Identifies the type of a file |\n\n---\n\n## ⚙️ SYSTEM & PROCESS MANAGEMENT\n\n| Command | How to Use | What It Does |\n|---------|------------|--------------|\n| `ps` | Type `ps` for your processes, `ps aux` for all processes | Lists running processes |\n| `top` | Just type `top`, press `q` to quit | Interactive process viewer |\n| `htop` | Type `htop` (may need to install), `q` to quit | Better looking process viewer |\n| `kill` | Type `kill 1234` where 1234 is the process ID | Stops a process |\n| `killall` | Type `killall firefox` to kill all Firefox processes | Kills processes by name |\n| `df` | Type `df -h` for human-readable sizes | Shows disk space usage |\n| `du` | Type `du -sh foldername` for folder size | Shows directory sizes |\n| `free` | Type `free -h` for human-readable | Shows memory usage |\n| `uptime` | Just type `uptime` | Shows how long system has been running |\n| `whoami` | Just type `whoami` | Shows your current username |\n| `id` | Just type `id` | Shows your user and group IDs |\n| `uname` | Type `uname -a` for all info | Shows system information |\n| `env` | Just type `env` | Lists all environment variables |\n| `history` | Just type `history` or `history | grep \"command\"` | Shows command history |\n| `clear` | Just type `clear` or press `Ctrl+L` | Clears the terminal screen |\n\n---\n\n## 🌐 NETWORKING\n\n| Command | How to Use | What It Does |\n|---------|------------|--------------|\n| `ping` | Type `ping google.com` then `Ctrl+C` to stop | Tests network connectivity |\n| `curl` | Type `curl https://api.example.com` or `curl -O URL` to download | Transfers data from URLs |\n| `wget` | Type `wget https://example.com/file.zip` | Downloads files from web |\n| `ssh` | Type `ssh username@server.com` | Securely connects to remote server |\n| `scp` | Type `scp file.txt user@host:/path/` | Securely copies files over network |\n| `rsync` | Type `rsync -avz local/ user@host:remote/` | Syncs files efficiently |\n| `netstat` | Type `netstat -tlnp` to see listening ports | Shows network connections |\n| `ss` | Type `ss -tlnp` (newer replacement for netstat) | Shows socket statistics |\n| `lsof` | Type `lsof -i :8080` to see what's using port 8080 | Lists open files and ports |\n| `ifconfig` | Type `ifconfig` or `ifconfig eth0` | Shows network interfaces |\n| `ip` | Type `ip addr` or `ip route` | Modern network configuration tool |\n| `traceroute` | Type `traceroute google.com` | Shows network path to destination |\n| `dig` | Type `dig google.com` | DNS lookup tool |\n| `nslookup` | Type `nslookup google.com` | Queries DNS servers |\n| `nc` | Type `nc -zv host 80` to test port 80 | Netcat - network testing tool |\n| `telnet` | Type `telnet host 80` | Tests TCP connections |\n\n---\n\n## 🔐 PERMISSIONS & OWNERSHIP\n\n| Command | How to Use | What It Does |\n|---------|------------|--------------|\n| `chmod` | Type `chmod 755 script.sh` or `chmod +x file` | Changes file permissions |\n| `chown` | Type `sudo chown user:group file.txt` | Changes file owner |\n| `sudo` | Type `sudo command` (enter password when asked) | Runs command as superuser |\n| `su` | Type `su - username` to switch users | Switches to another user |\n| `passwd` | Just type `passwd` and follow prompts | Changes your password |\n| `groups` | Type `groups` or `groups username` | Shows which groups you belong to |\n\n---\n\n## 📦 PACKAGE MANAGEMENT\n\n### Debian/Ubuntu (apt)\n| Command | How to Use | What It Does |\n|---------|------------|--------------|\n| `apt update` | Type `sudo apt update` | Updates the package list |\n| `apt upgrade` | Type `sudo apt upgrade` | Upgrades installed packages |\n| `apt install` | Type `sudo apt install nginx` | Installs a package |\n| `apt remove` | Type `sudo apt remove nginx` | Removes a package |\n| `apt search` | Type `apt search editor` | Searches for packages |\n\n### RHEL/CentOS (yum/dnf)\n| Command | How to Use | What It Does |\n|---------|------------|--------------|\n| `yum install` | Type `sudo yum install nginx` | Installs a package |\n| `dnf install` | Type `sudo dnf install nginx` | Installs a package (newer) |\n\n### Arch (pacman)\n| Command | How to Use | What It Does |\n|---------|------------|--------------|\n| `pacman -S` | Type `sudo pacman -S nginx` | Installs a package |\n| `pacman -R` | Type `sudo pacman -R nginx` | Removes a package |\n| `pacman -Sy` | Type `sudo pacman -Sy` | Updates package database |\n\n---\n\n## 🔧 ARCHIVE & COMPRESSION\n\n| Command | How to Use | What It Does |\n|---------|------------|--------------|\n| `tar` | Type `tar -czvf backup.tar.gz folder/` to create | Creates/extracts tar archives |\n| `tar` | Type `tar -xzvf backup.tar.gz` to extract | Extracts tar.gz files |\n| `gzip` | Type `gzip file.txt` | Compresses a file |\n| `gunzip` | Type `gunzip file.gz` | Decompresses a gzip file |\n| `zip` | Type `zip -r archive.zip folder/` | Creates zip archives |\n| `unzip` | Type `unzip archive.zip` | Extracts zip files |\n\n---\n\n## 🔄 JOB CONTROL\n\n| Command | How to Use | What It Does |\n|---------|------------|--------------|\n| `&` | Type `long-running-command &` | Runs command in background |\n| `bg` | Type `bg %1` to resume job 1 in background | Resumes suspended job in background |\n| `fg` | Type `fg %1` to bring job 1 to foreground | Brings background job to foreground |\n| `jobs` | Just type `jobs` | Lists background jobs |\n| `nohup` | Type `nohup command &` | Runs command that survives logout |\n|"}},{"type":"text","text":" `"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"dashscope-coding","model":"kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774853090101}}
