{"type":"message","id":"ec3790fe","parentId":"0a810a17","timestamp":"2026-03-30T06:51:21.900Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let me continue with the rest of the file:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"functions.edit:26","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/admin/.openclaw/workspace/terminal-commands.md","old_string":"| `nohup` | Type `nohup command &` | Runs command that survives logout |\n|","new_string":"| `nohup` | Type `nohup command &` | Runs command that survives logout |\n| `disown` | Type `disown %1` | Removes job from shell's control |\n| `screen` | Type `screen -S mysession` then `Ctrl+A D` to detach | Terminal multiplexer |\n| `tmux` | Type `tmux new -s mysession` then `Ctrl+B D` to detach | Modern terminal multiplexer |\n\n---\n\n## 🔗 REDIRECTION & PIPES\n\n| Operator | How to Use | What It Does |\n|----------|------------|--------------|\n| `>` | Type `command > file.txt` | Saves output to file (overwrites) |\n| `>>` | Type `command >> file.txt` | Appends output to file |\n| `2>` | Type `command 2> error.log` | Saves errors to file |\n| `&>` | Type `command &> all.log` | Saves output and errors to file |\n| `<` | Type `command < input.txt` | Uses file as input |\n| `\\|` | Type `cat file \\| grep \"word\"` | Sends output to next command |\n| `\\|\\|` | Type `cmd1 \\|\\| cmd2` | Runs cmd2 only if cmd1 fails |\n| `&&` | Type `cmd1 && cmd2` | Runs cmd2 only if cmd1 succeeds |\n| `;` | Type `cmd1 ; cmd2` | Runs commands one after another |\n\n---\n\n## 🛠️ ADVANCED / LESSER-USED COMMANDS\n\n| Command | How to Use | What It Does |\n|---------|------------|--------------|\n| `strace` | Type `strace -p 1234` to trace process 1234 | Traces system calls of a process |\n| `ltrace` | Type `ltrace ./program` | Traces library calls |\n| `perf` | Type `perf top` to see CPU usage by function | Linux performance analyzer |\n| `vmstat` | Type `vmstat 1` to report every second | Reports virtual memory statistics |\n| `iostat` | Type `iostat -x 1` for extended stats every second | Reports I/O statistics |\n| `mpstat` | Type `mpstat -P ALL 1` for all CPUs | Reports CPU statistics per core |\n| `sar` | Type `sar -u 1` for CPU usage every second | System activity reporter |\n| `dmesg` | Type `dmesg \\| tail` or `dmesg -w` to watch | Views kernel messages |\n| `journalctl` | Type `journalctl -xe` for recent errors with explanations | Views systemd logs |\n| `systemctl` | Type `systemctl status nginx` or `systemctl restart nginx` | Controls systemd services |\n| `watch` | Type `watch -n 1 'ps aux \\| grep nginx'` | Runs command repeatedly |\n| `timeout` | Type `timeout 5s slow-command` | Runs command with time limit |\n| `nice` | Type `nice -n 10 command` | Runs with lower CPU priority |\n| `renice` | Type `renice -n 5 -p 1234` | Changes priority of running process |\n| `chroot` | Type `sudo chroot /newroot /bin/bash` | Changes root directory |\n| `mount` | Type `sudo mount /dev/sdb1 /mnt` | Mounts a filesystem |\n| `umount` | Type `sudo umount /mnt` | Unmounts a filesystem |\n| `fdisk` | Type `sudo fdisk -l` to list, `sudo fdisk /dev/sda` to edit | Partition table manipulator |\n| `parted` | Type `sudo parted /dev/sda` | Partition editor |\n| `mkfs` | Type `sudo mkfs.ext4 /dev/sdb1` | Creates a filesystem |\n| `fsck` | Type `sudo fsck /dev/sdb1` | Checks and repairs filesystem |\n| `dd` | Type `dd if=/dev/zero of=file.img bs=1M count=100` | Low-level copy/convert |\n| `tee` | Type `command \\| tee file.txt` | Saves output and shows it |\n| `xargs` | Type `find . -name \"*.log\" \\| xargs rm` | Builds commands from input |\n| `parallel` | Type `parallel echo ::: 1 2 3` | Runs commands in parallel |\n| `at` | Type `echo \"backup.sh\" \\| at midnight` | Schedules one-time task |\n| `cron` | Type `crontab -e` to edit, `crontab -l` to list | Schedules recurring tasks |\n| `logger` | Type `logger \"Something happened\"` | Writes to system log |\n| `script` | Type `script session.log` then `exit` when done | Records terminal session |\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"dashscope-coding","model":"kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774853441180}}
