{"type":"message","id":"888abca5","parentId":"67638c84","timestamp":"2026-03-30T06:55:34.022Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## ⚙️ SYSTEM & PROCESS MANAGEMENT\n\n| Command | How to Use | What It Does |\n|---------|------------|--------------|\n| `ps` | Type `ps` for your processes, `ps aux` for all processes | Lists running processes |\n| `top` | Just type `top`, press `q` to quit | Interactive process viewer |\n| `htop` | Type `htop` (may need to install), `q` to quit | Better looking process viewer |\n| `kill` | Type `kill 1234` where 1234 is the process ID | Stops a process |\n| `killall` | Type `killall firefox` to kill all Firefox processes | Kills processes by name |\n| `df` | Type `df -h` for human-readable sizes | Shows disk space usage |\n| `du` | Type `du -sh foldername` for folder size | Shows directory sizes |\n| `free` | Type `free -h` for human-readable | Shows memory usage |\n| `uptime` | Just type `uptime` | Shows how long system has been running |\n| `whoami` | Just type `whoami` | Shows your current username |\n| `id` | Just type `id` | Shows your user and group IDs |\n| `uname` | Type `uname -a` for all info | Shows system information |\n| `env` | Just type `env` | Lists all environment variables |\n| `history` | Just type `history` or `history | grep \"command\"` | Shows command history |\n| `clear` | Just type `clear` or press `Ctrl+L` | Clears the terminal screen |\n\n---\n\n## 🌐 NETWORKING\n\n| Command | How to Use | What It Does |\n|---------|------------|--------------|\n| `ping` | Type `ping google.com` then `Ctrl+C` to stop | Tests network connectivity |\n| `curl` | Type `curl https://api.example.com` or `curl -O URL` to download | Transfers data from URLs |\n| `wget` | Type `wget https://example.com/file.zip` | Downloads files from web |\n| `ssh` | Type `ssh username@server.com` | Securely connects to remote server |\n| `scp` | Type `scp file.txt user@host:/path/` | Securely copies files over network |\n| `rsync` | Type `rsync -avz local/ user@host:remote/` | Syncs files efficiently |\n| `netstat` | Type `netstat -tlnp` to see listening ports | Shows network connections |\n| `ss` | Type `ss -tlnp` (newer replacement for netstat) | Shows socket statistics |\n| `lsof` | Type `lsof -i :8080` to see what's using port 8080 | Lists open files and ports |\n| `ifconfig` | Type `ifconfig` or `ifconfig eth0` | Shows network interfaces |\n| `ip` | Type `ip addr` or `ip route` | Modern network configuration tool |\n| `traceroute` | Type `traceroute google.com` | Shows network path to destination |\n| `dig` | Type `dig google.com` | DNS lookup tool |\n| `nslookup` | Type `nslookup google.com` | Queries DNS servers |\n| `nc` | Type `nc -zv host 80` to test port 80 | Netcat - network testing tool |\n| `telnet` | Type `telnet host 80` | Tests TCP connections |\n\n---\n\nContinue?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"dashscope-coding","model":"kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774853710446}}
